# AgentTask TODO (Compatibility Alias)

This file exists to keep historical tooling and documentation references working.

- Canonical backlog: `agentaskit-production/.todo`
- Subject intake inbox: `agentaskit-production/agentask.subject.todo`
- Execution SOP: `agentaskit-production/agentask.sop`
- Completion ledger: `agentaskit-production/core/src/orchestration/sot.md`

### Unified TODO Workflow (Summary)
1. Capture new subjects in `agentask.subject.todo` with `[REF]`, context tags, and evidence expectations.
2. Apply the 4D methodology; when ready, promote the subject into `.todo` with full owner/deps/acc/evid fields.
3. Execute changes under `agentask.sop` and the Update & Heal prompt, gathering hashes and transcripts.
4. Mark the `.todo` item complete, append the executed-task record to `sot.md`, and mirror closure back in the subject inbox.

> All automation, CI validations, and documentation should reference `.todo` as the single source of backlog truth.
